network_overview: Capture contains only two user-plane micro-flows (one 3-packet TCP/80 handshake, one 53-byte UDP probe) on private IP space; no mobile control-plane or voice protocols are present. The trace is therefore limited to post-tunnel IP traffic on an SGi/N6 or backhaul OAM segment.

observations.finding: Single TCP three-way handshake (SYN-SYN/ACK-ACK) completed in 1.7 ms between 192.168.1.1:1234 and 192.168.1.2:80 with 80 bytes total.
observations.evidence: Flow #1: 3 pkts, 162 bytes, flags [S, SA, A], duration 0.0017 s

observations.finding: Isolated 53-byte UDP/5000→6000 packet between 10.0.0.1 and 10.0.0.2 with no follow-up; likely OAM heartbeat.
observations.evidence: Flow #2: 1 pkt, 53 bytes, UDP, no retransmits

inconclusive_aspects.additional_capture_needed: Capture on S1-MME, N2, S5-C, N4, or Rx/Gm interfaces

recommendations.action: Re-capture on a signaling-visible interface (S1-MME, N2, S5-C, N4, or P-CSCF) to evaluate control-plane health.
recommendations.rationale: Current trace lacks any 3GPP control messages required to determine session success.

recommendations.action: Enable GTP-U decode on the probe or mirror S1-U/N3 user-plane to confirm bearer presence and RTP flow.
recommendations.rationale: Media-plane visibility is mandatory for voice-quality diagnosis.
